credit_line: Gift of Mrs. Adrienne A. Sheridan
title: Sidewall
provenance: From the George Collins house (now Galle or Gallet) in Unionvale, Dutchess County, east of Poughkeepsie, built about 1840. Used in the drawing room ofdonor's great, great-grandfather's house. See property file for donor's letter.
description: Against a glazed off-white ground is printed an elaborately scrolled single medallion enclosing a stencilled urn of gold leaf. Half borders of simple scrolls in grisaille at both edges of paper.
name: Sidewall
